devdoc.author: HELLO Chris
devdoc.details: Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to specific functions. By default, the owner account will be the one that deploys the contract. This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier `onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to the owner.

addProposal(string).details: Only registered voters can add a proposal.

params._description: : Proposal's description. Emits a {ProposalRegistered} event. Requirements: - `WorkflowStatus` must be at the ProposalsRegistrationStarted state. - `Description` can't be empty. - `Max length` = 50 proposals.

addVoter(address).details: Only the owner can call the function.

params._address: : address of the voter. Emits a {VoterRegistered} event. Requirements: - `WorkflowStatus` must be at the RegisteringVoters state. - `voter` cannot be already registered.

endProposalsRegistering().details: Current status must be RegisteringVoters.  Emits a {WorkflowStatusChange} event.

endVotingSession().details: Current status must be VotingSessionStarted.  Emits a {WorkflowStatusChange} event.

getOneProposal(uint256).details: Only registered voters can call the function.

returns._0: returns the proposal's structure (string: description ,uint256: voteCount).

getVoter(address).details: Only registered voters can call the function.

returns._0: returns the voter's structure (bool: isRegistered, bool: hasVoted, uint256: votedProposalId).

getWinningProposalId().details: Only owner can call this function.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

startProposalsRegistering().details: Current status must be RegisteringVoters.  Emits a {WorkflowStatusChange} event.

startVotingSession().details: Current status must be ProposalsRegistrationEnded.  Emits a {WorkflowStatusChange} event.

tallyVotes().details: Current status must be VotingSessionEnded Emits a {WorkflowStatusChange} event. Requirements: - `WorkflowStatus` must be at the VotingSessionEnded state. - `Max length` = 50 proposals.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

vote(uint256).details: Only registered voters can vote. Voters can vote only once.

params._proposalId: : id of the proposal. Emits a {Voted} event. Requirements: - `WorkflowStatus` must be at the VotingSessionStarted state. - `voter` cannot have already voted.

winningProposalId.details: By default this will be set to 0. Visibility is set to public to let anyone get the winning proposal ID.

workflowStatus.details: By default this will be set to 0 (RegisteringVoters). Public visibility is set to let anyone read the current status of the workflow.
